  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rapid response to address the emergency needs of drought impacted farming households in southern Somalia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this FAO project is to improve household food security and restore own food production among 8,220 rural households in Hiraan. 
With this 4 million USD CERF grant, FAO will provide sorghum, cowpea and vegetable seed along with tools (hoes and forks), fertilizers and storage bags through agriculture vouchers. 
The project covers food security sector and will last six months. It will benefit 49,320 persons including 11,030 girls and 12,333 women.</narrative>
  </description>
